Dallas BROOKS, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D18-3288 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. October 09, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

Petitioner's petition for writ of mandamus is denied without prejudice to any right petitioner might have to request counsel in the lower tribunal. See Fla. R. Crim. P. 3.850(f)(7) ; Graham v. State, 372 So. 2d 1363 (Fla. 1979).

LaROSE, C.J., and MORRIS and SALARIO, JJ., Concur.
